        "content": "<p>new to lean, not sure how to express ℝⁿ.</p>\n<p>specifically I want to be able to take an object of this type, and multiply matrices against it. but it sounds messy to make this type a subset of matrices that restricts the row count to 1. is there maybe an ℝⁿ type that has an easy conversion to column matrices?</p>",
        "id": 503961070,
        "sender_full_name": "Becker A.",
        "timestamp": 1741329257
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=EuclideanSpace#doc\">docs#EuclideanSpace</a> is one option, it depends on what you want to do more exactly</p>",
        "id": 503970642,
        "sender_full_name": "Luigi Massacci",
        "timestamp": 1741329781
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Otherwise even just <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Fin</mtext><mtext> </mtext><mi>n</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{Fin} \\,n \\to \\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">Fin</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span></span></span> will also work (if you don't care about topological aspects)</p>",
        "id": 503970956,
        "sender_full_name": "Luigi Massacci",
        "timestamp": 1741329929
    },
